  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal money laundering charges\n- Potential prison time (typically 10-20 years)\n- Significant financial penalties/fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Seizure of assets related to illegal activities\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential forfeit of property\n\n3. Additional Legal Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n\n4. Potential Prosecution\n- Federal prosecutors typically handle money laundering cases\n- Charges can be brought at state and federal levels\n\nThe specific consequences depend on the amount of money involved, jurisdiction, and specific circumstances of the case.",
